President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in Rhode Island due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred from January 28 to January 29, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, snow assistance, and hazard mitigation measures. Deanne Criswell, Administrator of FEMA, has named William F. Roy as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.